        <div class="guarantee" style="width: 100%">
            <h4 style="text-align: center;">PERSONAL GUARANTEE &amp; INDEMNITY</h4>
            <p>THIS GUARANTEE and INDEMNITY is made the ___________ day of _____________________ 20_______________</p>
            <p>To: Rainbow Agroscience Australia Pty Ltd (ACN 160 656 431) including any current or future related body corporate or related entity as defined in the Corporations Act 2001 (Cth) their successors in title, transferees and assigns <span style="font-weight: bold;">(“Supplier/s”)</span>.</p>
            <p>To <span style="font-weight: bold;">THE INDEBTEDNESS TO THE SUPPLIERS</span></p>
            <p>of (entity name) __________________________________________________________________________________</p>
            <p>ACN (if any)__________________________________________ABN__________________________________________</p>
            <p>Of (address)_______________________________________________________________________________________</p>
            <p>(hereinafter called “<span style="font-weight: bold;">the Applicant</span>”) </p>
            <p>In consideration of credit being approved by the Suppliers at our request in favour of the Applicant, we the signatories to this document ("<span style="font-weight: bold;">the Guarantors</span>") which expression shall mean and include our respective heirs, executors, administrators and assigns HEREBY:</p>
            <table class="double-col">
                <tr>
                    <td style="width: 50%; vertical-align: top; padding-right: 10px">
                        1.	I/We guarantee payment to the Supplier of the whole price charged by the Supplier for Goods or Services supplied to the Applicant from time to time, without any deduction or setoff whatsoever. I/We also guarantee payment of any other monies now or in the future owing by the Applicant to the Supplier. I/We also guarantee the performance of the obligations of the Applicant pursuant to the Hire Agreement.<br/>
                        2.	I/We indemnify the Supplier against all costs, losses and expenses which the Supplier incurs as a result of any default by the Applicant. I/We agree to pay any stamp duty assessed on this Guarantee.<br/>
                        3.	My/Our guarantee and indemnity under this Guarantee is a continuing guarantee and will not be affected:<br/>
                        (a)	if the Supplier grants any extension of time or other indulgence to the Applicant or varies the terms of the Applicant's account (even if this increases my/our liability under this Guarantee);<br/>
                        (b)	by the release of any of the Guarantors or if this Guarantee is or becomes unenforceable against one or more of the Guarantors;<br/>
                        (c)	any payment by the Applicant being later avoided by law, whether or not I/we have been given notice of these matters;<br/>
                        4.	I/We agree that an application for credit made by the Applicant is deemed to have been accepted from the date of the first invoice by the Supplier to the Applicant and, without further notice to me/us, this Guarantee will extend to all liabilities from the Applicant to that Supplier.<br/>
                        5.	This Guarantee extends to credit given to the Applicant in the future by a company which is not now, but at the time such credit is extended, is a related entity of the Supplier.<br/>
                        6.	This Guarantee may be withdrawn by the Guarantor(s) on expiry of 14 days following written notice of withdrawal being delivered to both the Supplier's Company Secretary at the Supplier's registered office. This Guarantee will continue in force in respect of all debt incurred up to the date of withdrawal.<br/>
                        7.	I/We authorise the Supplier to do each of the things listed in the Privacy Disclosure and Consent section of the credit application in relation to my/our personal credit matters.<br/>
                        8.(a)As security for the obligations and liabilities of the Guarantor(s), I/we charge for the due and punctual payment and performance of those obligations and liabilities, all of my/ our legal and equitable interest (including as beneficial owner, both present and future) of whatsoever nature held in any and all real property owned by me/ us now or in the future, solely or jointly in favour of the Supplier.<br/>
                        (b)	Without limiting the generality of the charge in clause 8(a), I/we agree on request by the Supplier to execute any documents and do all things reasonably required by the Supplier to register a mortgage security over any real property. In the event that the Guarantor(s) fails to deliver the requested documents, the Guarantor(s) hereby appoints the Supplier to be the Guarantor's(s') lawful attorney for the purposes of executing and registering such documents. I/We indemnify the Supplier on an indemnity basis against all costs and expenses incurred by the Supplier in connection with the preparation and registration of such mortgage documents.<br/>
                        (c)	I/We consent unconditionally to the Supplier lodging a caveat or caveats noting its interest in any real property.<br/>
                        (d)	We agree to advise the Supplier in writing of the occurrence of any Insolvency Event, any change in my/our name, ownership or control, or any step being taken to sell an asset or assets (separately or together
                    </td>
                    <td style="width: 50%; vertical-align: top; padding-left: 10px">
                        having a value being greater than 20% in value of my/our gross assets) as soon as practicable and not later than within two business days of such event, change or step occurring.<br/>
                        (e)	If any payment made by or on behalf of the Applicant is alleged to be void or voidable by any liquidator or like officer of the Applicant under any law related to insolvency, I/we indemnify the Supplier against any costs or losses it may incur in connection with such claim. This indemnity shall continue to apply notwithstanding any withdrawal under clause 6.<br/>
                        (f)	If the charge created by clause 8(a) is or becomes void or unenforceable, it may be severed from this Guarantee without any effect on the Supplier's rights against the Guarantor(s).<br/>
                        (g)	If the Guarantor(s) is a trustee of a trust, the Guarantor(s) enters into this agreement in both the Guarantor's personal capacity and as trustee of that trust.<br/>
                        9.	Any condition or agreement under this Guarantee by or in favour of two or more persons is deemed to bind them jointly and severally, or be in favour of each of them severally. If the Guarantor comprises more than one person the Supplier may at any time, and from time to time, proceed against any or all of them in respect of the Guarantor's obligations as the Supplier may choose in its absolute discretion, and the Supplier is not to be obliged to make any claim against all the persons comprising the Guarantor.<br/>
                        10.	Until the whole of the Applicant's obligations have been paid or satisfied in full, the Guarantor(s) must not (except with the prior written consent of the Supplier) either directly or indirectly, and either before or after the winding up or bankruptcy of the Applicant, or any person, take any steps to recover or enforce a right or claim against the Applicant relating to any sum paid by the Guarantor to the Supplier under this Guarantee including without limitation proving or claiming in competition with the Supplier so as to diminish any distribution, dividend or payment which, but for the proof or claim, the Supplier would be entitled to receive pursuant to the winding up or bankruptcy of the Applicant.<br/>
                        11.	Singular words include the plural and vice versa and references to any party to this Guarantee, include that party's executors, administrators, substitutes, successors or permitted assigns<br/>
                        Goods means any goods supplied by the Supplier being plant and equipment, machinery related to mining and civil services and all related or ancillary goods.<br/>
                        Insolvency Event means, for the Applicant, as applicable, being in liquidation or provisional liquidation, bankruptcy or under administration, having a controller (as defined in the Corporations Act 2001) or analogous person appointed to the Applicant or any of the Applicant's property, being unable to pay the Applicant's debts, dying, ceasing to be of full legal capacity or otherwise becoming incapable of managing the Applicant's own affairs for any reason, taking any step that could result in the Company becoming an insolvent under administration (as defined in section 9 of the Corporations Act 2001), entering into a compromise or arrangement with, or assignment for the benefit of, any of the Applicant's members or creditors, or any analogous event.<br/>
                        Services means any services provided by the Supplier being the supply of personnel for the operation of plant and equipment, consulting and professional services relating to mining and civil services and all related or ancillary services.
                    </td>
                </tr>
            </table>
